# Supabase Security

- Enable Row Level Security on every user-data table in exposed schemas, especially `public`.
- For personal task data, include an owner column such as `user_id uuid not null references auth.users(id)` and scope policies with `auth.uid() = user_id`.
- Write separate policies for `select`, `insert`, `update`, and `delete` when access rules differ.
- Remember that `update` also needs a matching `select` policy, or updates can return no rows.
- Browser code may use only the Supabase URL and publishable/anon key.
- Never place `service_role`, secret keys, database passwords, or private API tokens in Vue/Vite browser code.
- Do not use user-editable metadata for authorization. Store authorization data in app metadata or tables protected by RLS.
- If views are exposed, prefer `security_invoker = true` on supported Postgres versions so RLS is honored.
